Name: point of origin Marketing Consulting & Consumer intelligence GmbH
Positive Thinking  Company (Austria)
Description:
“We are a global tech group that delivers end-to-end tech solutions through a global delivery model. At Positive Thinking Company, we aim to create positive business outcomes that support our clients through their ever-changing business environments so they can thrive in our global economy.

We invest our efforts in unlocking the full potential of not only our clients, but also that of our coworkers by providing them an evolutive environment encouraging collaboration, creativity and positive mindset.

To meet our client’s present and future challenges we offer a global delivery approach. This hybrid model, leveraging both local and global delivery centers, allows our customers to access flexible delivery options and find the best balance between proximity, cost, quality and risk.

Through 3,000 local tech specialists on the ground in over 35 cities across Europe, the USA, Asia, Australia and Africa, we offer a full portfolio of services that draw on a wide array of expertise, including apps & platforms, security, cloud, data & analytics, hyperautomation and digital workplace.

The industries that benefit include, among others, banking and financial services, insurance, healthcare, retail, transportation, telecom and public sector. We serve each of them with a meaningful and collaborative mindset, always keeping at heart our historic motto: Collaboration betters our world.

Positive Thinking Company – let’s do something great together”
Certifications: SAS Certified Data Quality Steward for SAS 9, SAS Certified Data Integration Developer for SAS 9, SAS Certified Visual Business Analyst Exploration and Design Using SAS Visual Analytics, SAS Certified Platform Administrator for SAS 9, SAS Certified Base Programmer for SAS 9, SAS Certified Statistical Business Analyst Using SAS 9 Regression and Modeling, SAS 9.4 Business Analytics Platform Deployment Practical Certification, SAS Certified Predictive Modeler using Enterprise Miner 13, SAS Certified Advanced Programmer for SAS 9, SAS Certified Visual Analytics Deployment Specialist Using SAS 9 Certification Exam
Additional Experience: Analytic Modernization, Customer Intelligence, Fraud (Security Intelligence), Risk Management
Industries: Manufacturing, Energy and Utilities, Financial Services, Retail, Telecommunications, Public Sector/Government, Health Care and Life Sciences, Education, Insurance, Pharmaceutical

Name: Prisma Srl
Description: Prisma is an Italian ICT Company leader in designing, realizing and selling products, solutions and innovative systems for security, telecommunications, defense, transportation, information technology and environment. Prisma was born as a company operating in the Information Technology field, offering software development solutions and IT professional services, today is a benchmark for web-oriented companies in the design, realization and evolution of ICT solutions aimed to bring added value to the infrastructure and the business processes, this leveraging our process and technological skills, as well as our managerial and organisational competencies. Nowadays, Prisma counts about 180 professionals, with competencies developed in various business areas and professional fields. High-qualified technical support, minimizing project risks and guaranteeing high quality of integrated solutions. Prisma offers a wide range of solutions and interventions designed to provide its customers with a stable competitive advantage, thanks to the setting and sharing of corporate strategies and their rapid implementation through processes, organization and supporting information tools. BUSINESS UNITS Consulting: Develops and supports the realization of winning strategies, turning market changes into a competitive advantage for Customers. It offers and implements solutions for the continuous improvement of performances, guaranteeing metrics of the results achieved. Technology: Develops IT solutions in line with the organizational model and the Company’s actual needs. This through the implementation of architecturally and technologically innovative solutions, which act on the critical processes and solve company critical issues. Digital marketing: Helps Customers improving sales performance and user experience, through the support of advanced web analysis and web optimization tools. It supplies specialized professional services in the design and implementation of e-commerce portals, mobile apps and social, on top of services and solutions for digital marketing and advertising. A consolidated creative team, made up of certified professionals, can offer a highly specialized consultancy service. This thanks to consolidated partnerships with key technology vendors for the analysis and optimization of the digital world (Adobe, Webtrends, Tealium, IBM, ORACLE,SAS). We offer some among the most advanced solutions available in the marketplace, and we supply specialized professional services for this tools, supporting the analysis and implementation of communication campaigns and digital marketing strategies.

Name: Protinus IT BV
Description:
We make the difference for our customers in a market that has traditionally had a rigid distribution chain with many restrictions for you as a customer. We do offer the necessary agility and remove the limitations through a smart way of making connections between customer and supplier: Find Connect Amplify.
With the help of our extensive partner network, we link your needs to the best solutions within the 4 quadrants as we have classified IT: hardware, software, human skills and practices.
The focus is on organizations with 1,000+ workplaces. Our customers are mainly active in the public sector: central government, decentralized government (provinces and municipalities), education and healthcare.
